Message.MsgText: MDBListenerCreateException=WMSG0006E: Error creating MDBListener for JMS Listener {0}, JMSDestination {1} : {2}
Message.Explanation: An exception was received while trying to create the MDBListener instance for the given JMS Listener.
Message.UserResponse: Determine from the given exception the reason that the MDBListener was not created. Examine your JMS Listener configuration file to ensure the definition is correct, and ensure that all the necessary JMS resources are bound into the WebSphere JNDI name space. Also, ensure that the necessary JMS provider classes are in the application server class path.

Message.MsgText: JMSListenerInitializeMDBException=WMSG0003E: Error initializing JMSListenerStub: {0}
Message.Explanation: An exception was received while trying to initialize the JMS Listener.
Message.UserResponse: Determine from the given exception the reason that the JMS Listener has not initialized.

Message.MsgText: INCORRECT_ACT_SEPC_TYPE_WMSG3010=WMSG3010E: The activate endpoint method was called with an activation specification of type {1} when a type of {0} is expected.
Message.Explanation: An incorrect activation specification class was passed to the endpointActivation method of the resource adapter wrapper.
Message.UserResponse: When using the resource adapter wrapper, ensure that the correct activation specification class is passed to the endpointActivation method

Message.MsgText: PCFCommandServerInvalidSettingTypeReturned=WMSG0318E: The Command Server has returned some attributes of the incorrect type.
Message.Explanation: While unpacking the response from the queue manager an incorrect type was found.
Message.UserResponse: Try again later.

Message.MsgText: MDBListenerDuplicate=WMSG0022E: Duplicate MDBListener definition for {0}, JMSDestination {1}
Message.Explanation: An attempt has been made to define a duplicate JMS Listener in the configuration file.
Message.UserResponse: Correct the JMS Listener configuration file to remove the duplicate entry, then restart the EJB Server to re-initialize the JMS Listener.

Message.MsgText: MQ_INSTALL_ROOT_VERSION_HAS_CHANGED_WMSG1626=WMSG1626W: The WebSphere MQ messaging provider installed at {0} has been updated from version {1} to version {2}. A server restart may be required to properly register this update.
Message.Explanation: Service has been applied to the WebSphere MQ messaging provider which has changed its version number.
Message.UserResponse: The application server may need to be restarted in order to properly register the new WebSphere MQ messaging provider code with the application server.

Message.MsgText: JMS_REGISTRATION_UNSUPPORTED_VERSION_WMSG1624=WMSG1624E: It was not possible to use the specified WebSphere MQ messaging provider at path {0} because it is at version {1}. The minimum supported version is {2}.
Message.Explanation: The WebSphere MQ messaging provider code installed at the specified path is at a level that is lower than the minimum level supported and so can not be used.
Message.UserResponse: Modify the configuration of the WebSphere MQ messaging provider in the application server so it points to a supported level of the WebSphere MQ messaging provider. This will involve either changing the contents or install directory of the WebSphere MQ resource adapter or changing the value of the MQ_INSTALL_ROOT variable. Then restart your application server.

Message.MsgText: PCFCommandServerQueueNameNotValid=WMSG0319E: The Queue name you have specified is invalid.
Message.Explanation: The queue name specified is not valid.
Message.UserResponse: Correct the name of the queue.

Message.MsgText: JMSSessionRunException=WMSG0031E: Exception processing JMS Message for MDB {0}, JMSDestination {1} : {2}
Message.Explanation: During the processing of a JMS message an unexpected exception was received.
Message.UserResponse: Examine the exception for reasons for the problem. After correction restart the MDB EJB JAR module from the administrative console.

Message.MsgText: MQQueueDefinerClusterNameTooLong=WMSG0120I: Cluster name is over 48 characters long. reason = {0}, parameter = {1}.
Message.Explanation: The cluster name specified is longer than 48 characters.
Message.UserResponse: Ensure that the cluster name contains less than 48 characters.

Message.MsgText: MDBListenerStartException=WMSG0019E: Unable to start MDB Listener {0}, JMSDestination {1} : {2}
Message.Explanation: An exception has occurred during the start of the given MDB Listener.
Message.UserResponse: Examine the exception for reasons for the problem, then restart the MDB EJB JAR module from the administrative console.

Message.MsgText: JMSConfigParseErrors=WMSG0012E: Errors parsing JMS Listener config file: {0}, {1}
Message.Explanation: An error was issued trying to parse the given JMS Listener configuration file.
Message.UserResponse: Correct the problem in the JMS Listener configuration file, then restart the EJB Server.

Message.MsgText: JMSListenerFailedToStart=WMSG0041E: JMS Listener failed to start
Message.Explanation: The JMS Listener service was unable to start because of some initialization errors.
Message.UserResponse: Examine the error logs to determine the cause of the problem,correct any errors then restart the server.

Message.MsgText: MQ_INSTALL_ROOT_VERSION_HAS_CHANGED_WMSG1613=WMSG1613W: The WebSphere MQ installed at {0} has been updated from version {1} to version {2}. A server restart may be required to properly register this update.
Message.Explanation: Service has been applied to the WebSphere MQ install used by WebSphere Application Server.
Message.UserResponse: The application server may need to be restarted in order to properly register the new client with the application server.

Message.MsgText: JMS_REGISTRATION_UNSUPPORTED_VERSION_WMSG1604=WMSG1604E: It was not possible to use the specified WebSphere MQ JMS client at path {0} because it is at version {1}, the minimum supported version is {2}.
Message.Explanation: The MQ_INSTALL_ROOT variable has been configured to refer to a level of the WebSphere MQ JMS client that is not supported.
Message.UserResponse: Modify the MQ_INSTALL_ROOT variable to reference a supported level of the WebSphere MQ JMS client.

Message.MsgText: PCFCommandServerConnectionError=WMSG0320E: Internal Queue Manager error.
Message.Explanation: An internal exception has been created in the queue manager.
Message.UserResponse: Try again later.

Message.MsgText: MQQueueDefinerInvalidBackoutQueueName=WMSG0109I: Invalid backout Queue name specified. reason = {0}, parameter = {1}.
Message.Explanation: The backout queue name specified is not valid.
Message.UserResponse: Ensure that the backout queue name contains a valid value.

Message.MsgText: PCFCommandServerSelectorError=WMSG0311E: There has been a selector error.
Message.Explanation: There was an error in a selector.
Message.UserResponse: Try again later.

Message.MsgText: MQQueueDefinerInvalidClusterNameList=WMSG0108I: Invalid Cluster name list specified. reason = {0}, parameter = {1}.
Message.Explanation: The cluster name list specified is not valid.
Message.UserResponse: Ensure that the cluster name list contains a valid value.

Message.MsgText: EXCEPTION_BUILDING_REFERENCE_WMSG1301=WMSG1301E: An exception occurred building the reference for JNDI deployment of {0}
Message.Explanation: This exception is unexpected. The cause is not immediately known.
Message.UserResponse: If the problem persists, additional information might be available if you search for the message ID on the following Web sites: WebSphere Application Server Support page: http://www.ibm.com/software/webservers/appserv/was/support/ WebSphere Application Server for z/OS Support page: http://www.ibm.com/software/webservers/appserv/zos_os390/support/ .

Message.MsgText: JMSConfigParseWarnings=WMSG0011W: Warnings parsing JMS Listener config file: {0}, {1}
Message.Explanation: A warning was issued trying to parse the given JMS Listener configuration file.
Message.UserResponse: Correct the problem in the JMS Listener configuration file, then restart the EJB Server.

Message.MsgText: LoginException=WMSG0029E: Error during JMSListener server login for MDB {0}, JMSDestination {1} : {2}
Message.Explanation: During the login processing on a secure application server an unexpected exception was received.
Message.UserResponse: Examine the exception for reasons for the security problem. After correction restart the MDB EJB JAR module from the administrative console.

Message.MsgText: JMSConfigParseFatals=WMSG0013E: Errors parsing JMS Listener config file: {0}, {1}
Message.Explanation: An error was issued trying to parse the given JMS Listener configuration file.
Message.UserResponse: Correct the problem in the JMS Listener configuration file, then restart the EJB Server.

Message.MsgText: JMSConnectionException=WMSG0018E: Error on JMSConnection for MDB {0}, JMSDestination {1} : {2}
Message.Explanation: An exception has been reported by the JMS provider on a JMSConnection.
Message.UserResponse: Examine the exception for reasons for the problem, then restart the MDB EJB JAR module from the administrative console.

Message.MsgText: PCFQueueDataValueLessThanZero=WMSG0340E: The value specified was less than zero
Message.Explanation: A value was specified that is outside the valid range.
Message.UserResponse: Specify a number greater than or equal to zero.

Message.MsgText: PCFCommandQueueDepthNotANumber=WMSG0327E: The Queue Depth specified was not a valid number.
Message.Explanation: The queue depth specified is not a valid number.
Message.UserResponse: Enter a valid number for the queue depth then try again.

Message.MsgText: WMQ_DISABLED_WMSG1720=WMSG1720I: All WebSphere MQ functionality on this server has been disabled.
Message.Explanation: All WebSphere MQ functionality has been disabled on this server as a result of the 'disable WebSphere MQ functionality' check box being selected on a WebSphere MQ messaging provider panel at an appropriate scope. Alternatively the manageWMQ administrative command may have been used to disable WebSphere MQ functionality. As a result of this all WebSphere MQ messaging provider, WebSphere MQ link, WebSphere MQ client link and MQ server functionality has been disabled.
Message.UserResponse: None unless WebSphere MQ functionality is required, in which case clear the 'disable WebSphere MQ functionality' check box on the relevant WebSphere MQ messaging provider panel or make use of the manageWMQ administrative command.

Message.MsgText: PCFCommandServerQueueManagerQuiescing=WMSG0324E: The Queue Manager is inactive.
Message.Explanation: The queue manager is inactive. Perhaps it is waiting to be restarted.
Message.UserResponse: Wait for the queue manager to be restarted then try again.

Message.MsgText: ERROR_BUILDING_REFERENCE_WMSG1300=WMSG1300E: An error occurred building the reference for JNDI deployment of {0}. Error code {1} was returned from MQ with the error messages [{2}] and [{3}]
Message.Explanation: An exception was created while building a reference object for JNDI deployment. This indicates that there is an inconsistency in the resource definition.
Message.UserResponse: Check the XML definition of the resource.

Message.MsgText: PCFCommandServerInvalidSetting=WMSG0300E: The {0} setting was not a valid value.
Message.Explanation: One of the settings has a value that is not valid.
Message.UserResponse: Change the setting so it is valid.

Message.MsgText: PCFCommandServerInvaidQueueName=WMSG0304E: The Queue name you specified contained invalid characters.
Message.Explanation: The queue name specified was not valid.
Message.UserResponse: Change the queue name so it is a valid name.

Message.MsgText: QUEUE_NAME_TOO_LONG_WMSG1152=WMSG1152E: Unable to define JMS Destination {0} as the Queue name is too long - maximum length is {1} characters
Message.Explanation: The name of the queue is too long.
Message.UserResponse: Reduce the length of the queue name to the maximum number of characters allowed or less.

Message.MsgText: JMSListenerStubStartMDBException=WMSG0007E: Error starting JMSListenerStub: {0}
Message.Explanation: An exception was received while trying to start the JMS Listener.
Message.UserResponse: Determine from the given exception the reason why the JMS Listener did not start.

Message.MsgText: MQQueueDefinerInvalidRemoteQueueName=WMSG0111I: Invalid remote Queue name specified. reason = {0}, parameter = {1}.
Message.Explanation: The remote queue name specified is not valid.
Message.UserResponse: Ensure that the remote queue name contains a valid value.

Message.MsgText: CREATE_ENDPOINT_UNAVAILABLE_WMSG3080=WMSG3080E: The system called an unexpected method. The createEndpoint method was called on a message endpoint factory in the Control Region Adjunct on z/OS.
Message.Explanation: This exception is unexpected. The cause is not immediately known.
Message.UserResponse: If the problem persists, additional information might be available if you search for the message ID on the following Web sites: WebSphere Application Server Support page: http://www.ibm.com/software/webservers/appserv/was/support/ WebSphere Application Server for z/OS Support page: http://www.ibm.com/software/webservers/appserv/zos_os390/support/ .

Message.MsgText: PCFCommandServerQueueManagerNameError=WMSG0322E: The Queue Manager name was either invalid or not known.
Message.Explanation: The name specified for queue manager is either not valid or not known.
Message.UserResponse: Check that the queue manager name is valid and that the queue manager exists.

Message.MsgText: JMSSessionRollbackException=WMSG0034E: Exception rollingback JMS Session for MDB {0}, JMSDestination {1} : {2}
Message.Explanation: During the rollback of a JMS message an unexpected exception was received.
Message.UserResponse: Examine the exception for reasons for the problem and resolve the transaction using the administrative console. After correction restart the MDB EJB JAR module from the administrative console.

Message.MsgText: MDBListenerStopException=WMSG0020E: Unable to stop MDB Listener {0}, JMSDestination {1} : {2}
Message.Explanation: An exception has occurred when attempting to stop the given MDB Listener.
Message.UserResponse: Examine the exception for reasons for the problem, then try stopping the MDB EJB JAR module again from the administrative console.

Message.MsgText: MDBListenerStartFailed=WMSG0049E: Failed to start MDB {0} against listener port {1}
Message.Explanation: The MDB Listener did not start, while being bound to the given listener port.
Message.UserResponse: Examine the exception details to determine the reason for the problem, then restart the given listener port.

Message.MsgText: CANNOT_CREATE_CF_WMSG1610=WMSG1610E: An exception occurred instantiating a WebSphere MQ JCA RA type connection factory.
Message.Explanation: A WebSphere MQ JCA RA connection factory could not be created, and will not be bound into the WebSphere Application Server JNDI. It will not be available to applications.
Message.UserResponse: Examine the linked exception to determine why the connection factory could not be created. Correct the problem, if possible.

Message.MsgText: MQQueueDefinerUnrecognisedErrorTooLong=WMSG0123I: An error occurred that is not recognised. reason = {0}, parameter = {1}.
Message.Explanation: An exception was created for a problem that has not been recognized.
Message.UserResponse: Use the WebSphere MQ information center to identify the problem.

Message.MsgText: PCFCommandServerCommandFailed=WMSG0302E: The action you tried did not complete. Check the other errors to determine the cause.
Message.Explanation: The command did not complete successfully. There should be other error messages that describe the cause of the problem.
Message.UserResponse: Inspect the other error messages.

Message.MsgText: SAXParseException=WMSG0014E: Error parsing JMSListener config file: {0}, line: {1}, column: {2}, message: {3}
Message.Explanation: An exception was received while trying to parse the given JMS Listener configuration file.
Message.UserResponse: Correct the problem in the JMS Listener configuration file, then restart the EJB Server.

Message.MsgText: MQQueueDefinerInvalidTransmissionQueueName=WMSG0112I: Invalid transmission Queue name specified. reason = {0}, parameter = {1}.
Message.Explanation: The transmission queue name specified is not valid.
Message.UserResponse: Ensure that the transmission queue name contains a valid value.

Message.MsgText: PCFCommandServerPortNotANumber=WMSG0326E: The Port number specifed was not a valid number.
Message.Explanation: The Port number specified is not a valid number.
Message.UserResponse: Enter a valid number for the port then try again.

Message.MsgText: MDBListenerStopped=WMSG0043I: MDB Listener {0} stopped for JMSDestination {1}
Message.Explanation: The given MDB Listener has stopped.
Message.UserResponse: If the Listener has stopped unexpectedly, examine the application server logs for preceding error messages.

Message.MsgText: PCFCommandServerPriorityNotANumber=WMSG0330E: The specified priority was not a number.
Message.Explanation: The default priority specified was not valid number.
Message.UserResponse: Ensure that the default priority attribute contains a number.

Message.MsgText: PCFCommandServerQueueExists=WMSG0303E: The Queue you tried to create already existed.
Message.Explanation: The queue already existed.
Message.UserResponse: The queue was created elsewhere. Click OK again to modify the queue.

Message.MsgText: PCFCommandServerClusterSettingNotValid=WMSG0301E: The settings you chose would have made the Queue a cluster Queue and a transmission Queue.
Message.Explanation: The queue is a transmission queue and cannot also be defined as a cluster queue.
Message.UserResponse: Remove the cluster name or cluster name list settings so the queue is not a member of a cluster queue.

Message.MsgText: ServerSessionCreateException=WMSG0028E: Exception creating JMS ServerSession for MDB {0}, JMSDestination {1} : {2}
Message.Explanation: During the creation of a JMS ServerSession for a new MDB Listener an unexpected exception was received.
Message.UserResponse: Examine the exception for reasons for the problem. After correction restart the MDB EJB JAR module from the administrative console.

Message.MsgText: SessionPoolMaxConnectionsTooSmall=WMSG0056W: MDB Listener Port {0} maximum sessions size of {1} is greater than its JMS Connection Factory {2} Session Pool size of {3}, setting maximum sessions to {3}
Message.Explanation: A message-driven bean is being started against the given listener port. This port has a maximum sessions value larger than the size of the JMS Connection Factory Session Pool that it is configured to use. The MDB Listener will start using the Session Pool size.
Message.UserResponse: Increase the JMS Connection Factory Session Pool size, or decrease the listener port maximum sessions.

Message.MsgText: PCFCommandServerInvaidClusterName=WMSG0341E: The Cluster name you specified contained invalid characters.
Message.Explanation: The cluster name specified is not valid.
Message.UserResponse: Change the cluster name so it is a valid name.

Message.MsgText: JMSListenerInitializeFailed=WMSG0045E: JMS Listener initialization failed
Message.Explanation: The JMS Listener service could not initialize because of some previous errors.
Message.UserResponse: Examine the previous error messages to determine the cause of the problem,correct any errors then restart the server.

Message.MsgText: MQ_NATIVEPATH_WMSG1627=WMSG1627I: Native libraries for the WebSphere MQ messaging provider will be loaded from the following directory: {0}.
Message.Explanation: The WebSphere MQ messaging provider has determined that the specified directory will contain any native libraries that it needs. This message will be output even if no native libraries are available.
Message.UserResponse: No action is required.

Message.MsgText: PCFQueueDataValueTooLong=WMSG0346E: A value that was too long was specified.
Message.Explanation: A specified string value is too long.
Message.UserResponse: Specify a value that is not too long.

Message.MsgText: ResourceAdapterListenerPortNotValid=WMSG0064E: Unable to start message-driven bean (MDB) {0} against listener port {1}. It is not valid to specify a Java Message Service (JMS) resource adapter resource for a listener port; either use a different JMS resource with a listener port or use a default messaging JMS resource with an activation specification.
Message.Explanation: A message-driven bean is starting. This bean is bound to a listener port that specifies Java Naming Directory (JNDI) names for a JMS resource adapter. JMS resource adapters cannot be used by a listener port because they support activation specifications only.
Message.UserResponse: Either redeploy the message-driven bean against a default messaging JMS activation specification or redeploy the message-driven bean against a different JMS resource that supports listener ports.

Message.MsgText: JMSListenerInitializeException=WMSG0004E: Error initializing JMSListenerStub: {0}
Message.Explanation: An exception was received while trying to initialize the JMS Listener.
Message.UserResponse: Determine from the given exception the reason that the JMS Listener has not initialized.

Message.MsgText: JMSServerSessionStartException=WMSG0037E: Exception starting JMS ServerSession for MDB {0}, JMSDestination {1} : {2}
Message.Explanation: During the starting of a JMS ServerSession an unexpected exception was received.
Message.UserResponse: Examine the exception for reasons for the problem. After correction restart the MDB EJB JAR module from the administrative console.

Message.MsgText: PCFCommandServerUnexpectedIOError=WMSG0315E: Unexpected IO error occurred.
Message.Explanation: While sending a message an IO exception was created.
Message.UserResponse: Try again later.

Message.MsgText: RollbackException=WMSG0032E: Unable to rollback JMS ServerSession transaction for MDB {0}, JMSDestination {1} : {2}
Message.Explanation: During the rollback of a JMS message an unexpected exception was received.
Message.UserResponse: Examine the exception for reasons for the problem and resolve the transaction using the administrative console. After correction restart the MDB EJB JAR module from the administrative console.

Message.MsgText: DefaultMessagingListenerPortNotValid=WMSG0063E: Unable to start message-driven bean (MDB) {0} against listener port {1}. It is not valid to specify a default messaging Java Message Service (JMS) resource for a listener port; either use a different JMS resource with a listener port or use a default messaging JMS resource with an activation specification.
Message.Explanation: A message-driven bean is starting. This bean is bound to a listener port that specifies Java Naming Directory (JNDI) names for a default messaging JMS resource. Default messaging cannot be used by a listener port because it is a JMS resource adapter that supports activation specifications only.
Message.UserResponse: Either redeploy the message-driven bean against a default messaging JMS activation specification or redeploy the message-driven bean against a different JMS resource that supports listener ports.

Message.MsgText: MQQueueDefinerBackoutQueueNameTooLong=WMSG0118I: Backout Queue name is over 48 characters long. reason = {0}, parameter = {1}.
Message.Explanation: The backout queue name specified is longer than 48 characters.
Message.UserResponse: Ensure that the backout queue name contains less than 48 characters.

Message.MsgText: JMSListenerStarted=WMSG0001I: JMS Listener started successfully
Message.Explanation: The JMS Listener service has started successfully.
Message.UserResponse: No action is required.

Message.MsgText: MESSAGING_CLIENT_ONLY_WMSG1602=WMSG1602I: WebSphere MQ JMS Client only has been installed
Message.Explanation: WebSphere MQ JMS Server has not been installed on this node so will not be available.
Message.UserResponse: If a JMS server is to be started on this node, WebSphere MQ JMS Server must be installed.

Message.MsgText: BAD_CF_TYPE2_WMSG1609=WMSG1609E: An internal error occurred. Unexpected object type {0}.
Message.Explanation: This exception is unexpected. The cause is not immediately known.
Message.UserResponse: If the problem persists, additional information might be available if you search for the message ID on the following Web sites: WebSphere Application Server Support page: http://www.ibm.com/software/webservers/appserv/was/support/ WebSphere Application Server for z/OS Support page: http://www.ibm.com/software/webservers/appserv/zos_os390/support/ .

Message.MsgText: MDBInvocationException=WMSG0027E: Exception invoking MessageDrivenBean.onMessage() for MDB {0} : {1}
Message.Explanation: During the invocation of the MessageDrivenBean.onMessage() method an unexpected exception was received.
Message.UserResponse: Examine the exception for reasons for the problem. After correction restart the MDB EJB JAR module from the administrative console.

Message.MsgText: MQQueueDefinerUnknownParameterTooLong=WMSG0122I: Unknown Parameter is too long. reason = {0}, parameter = {1}.
Message.Explanation: The PCF response message claims a parameter was too long, but the parameter was not expected.
Message.UserResponse: Check that the correct parameter is being used. Reference the WebSphere MQ information center if necessary.

Message.MsgText: MQQueueDefinerInvalidQueueName=WMSG0105I: Invalid Queue name specified. reason = {0}, parameter = {1}.
Message.Explanation: The queue name specified is not valid.
Message.UserResponse: Ensure that the queue name attribute contains a valid value.

Message.MsgText: PCFCommandServerOpenFailed=WMSG0321E: Internal Queue Manager error.
Message.Explanation: An internal exception has been created in the queue manager.
Message.UserResponse: Try again later.

Message.MsgText: CheckDurableSubscriptionException=WMSG0050E: Exception checking JMS durable subscriptions {0}
Message.Explanation: The message listener service checks that the current set of durable subscriptions are still valid and do not need unsubscribing. An exception was received during this check.
Message.UserResponse: Examine the exception details to determine the reason for the problem, then restart the server.

Message.MsgText: MDBPooledThreadMDBException=WMSG0038E: Exception in MDBPooledThread: {0}
Message.Explanation: During the processing of a JMS message on a server thread an unexpected exception was received.
Message.UserResponse: Examine the exception for reasons for the problem. After correction restart the MDB EJB JAR module from the administrative console.

Message.MsgText: MDBSecurityNotConfigured=WMSG0025E: MessageDrivenBean does not have any security permissions configured
Message.Explanation: During the creation of an MDB Listener on a secure application server an exception was received that indicated the given message-driven bean did not have its security permissions set.
Message.UserResponse: Configure the MessageDrivenBean.onMessage() method access permissions for access by anyone or by the Server security ID.

Message.MsgText: PCFQueueDataValueNull=WMSG0336E: You specified a null value where a String was required.
Message.Explanation: A null was specified for one of the queue data values.
Message.UserResponse: Specify a value that is not null.

Message.MsgText: PCFCommandServerMaximumMessageLengthNotANumber=WMSG0328E: The Maximum Message Length specified was not a valid number.
Message.Explanation: The maximum message length specified was not a valid number.
Message.UserResponse: Enter a valid number for the maximum message length then try again.

Message.MsgText: MDBOnMessageException=WMSG0026E: Exception invoking MessageDrivenBean.onMessage() for MDB {0} : {1}
Message.Explanation: During the invocation of the MessageDrivenBean.onMessage() method an unexpected exception was received.
Message.UserResponse: Examine the exception for reasons for the problem. After correction restart the MDB EJB JAR module from the administrative console.

Message.MsgText: MQQueueDefinerInvalidQueueDescription=WMSG0106I: Invalid Queue description specified. reason = {0}, parameter = {1}.
Message.Explanation: The queue description specified is not valid.
Message.UserResponse: Ensure that the queue description attribute contains a valid value.

Message.MsgText: PCFCommandServerMQQueueNameNotSpecified=WMSG0332E: The Name of the MQ Queue is required by the WMQQueueDefiner MBean
Message.Explanation: The WMQQueueDefiner MBean was not supplied with a queue name.
Message.UserResponse: Specify the name of the MQ queue.

Message.MsgText: MDBListenerRetryLimitReached=WMSG0059E: Maximum restart retry count of {0} reached for Listener Port {1}
Message.Explanation: The given listener port has reached its retry limit for starting.
Message.UserResponse: Examine the reason for the problem. After correction restart the listener port from the administrative console.

Message.MsgText: MQQueueDefinerQueueDescriptionTooLong=WMSG0115I: Queue description is over 64 characters long. reason = {0}, parameter = {1}.
Message.Explanation: The queue description specified is longer than 64 characters.
Message.UserResponse: Ensure that the queue description contains less than 64 characters.

Message.MsgText: MDBUnknownProperty=WMSG0061W: An Internal error has occured. The activation config expected a param of type {2} but got a {1} in MDB {0}
Message.Explanation: This exception is unexpected. The cause is not immediately known.
Message.UserResponse: If the problem persists, additional information might be available if you search for the message ID on the following Web sites: WebSphere Application Server Support page: http://www.ibm.com/software/webservers/appserv/was/support/ WebSphere Application Server for z/OS Support page: http://www.ibm.com/software/webservers/appserv/zos_os390/support/ .

Message.MsgText: MQQueueDefinerRemoteQMGRNameTooLong=WMSG0119I: Remote Queue Manager name is over 48 characters long. reason = {0}, parameter = {1}.
Message.Explanation: The remote queue manager name specified is longer than 48 characters.
Message.UserResponse: Ensure that the remote queue manager name contains less than 48 characters.

Message.MsgText: JMSConfigParseException=WMSG0010E: Error parsing JMSListener config file: {0}, {1}
Message.Explanation: An exception was received while trying to parse the given JMS Listener configuration file.
Message.UserResponse: Correct the problem in the JMS Listener configuration file, then restart the EJB Server.

Message.MsgText: PCFCommandServerQueueNotEmpty=WMSG0310E: Deletion of the Queue failed as it contains some messages that could not be removed.
Message.Explanation: There were some messages on the queue that could not be purged.
Message.UserResponse: Try again later.

Message.MsgText: PCFCommandServerBackoutThresholdNotANumber=WMSG0329E: The Backout Threshold specified was not a valid number.
Message.Explanation: The backout threshold specified is not a valid number.
Message.UserResponse: Enter a valid number for the backout threshold then try again.

Message.MsgText: ReadRequestLogException=WMSG0055E: Exception reading the Late Response Message Consumer Log {0}, {1}
Message.Explanation: The late response message consumer was unable to read the given log file, because of an exception.
Message.UserResponse: Examine the exception details to determine why the log file could not be read.

Message.MsgText: CleanupDurableSubscriptionException=WMSG0052E: Exception unsubscribing JMS durable subscription {0} : {1}
Message.Explanation: When attempting to unsubscribe a durable subscription an exception was received.
Message.UserResponse: Examine the exception details to determine the reason for the problem, then restart the server.

Message.MsgText: PCFCommandServerUnexpectedPCFError=WMSG0306E: Unexpected error occurred. PCF reason code {0}, please check the WebSphere MQ documentation for a description of the error.
Message.Explanation: This exception is unexpected. The cause is not immediately known.
Message.UserResponse: If the problem persists, additional information might be available if you search for the message ID on the following Web sites: WebSphere Application Server Support page: http://www.ibm.com/software/webservers/appserv/was/support/ WebSphere Application Server for z/OS Support page: http://www.ibm.com/software/webservers/appserv/zos_os390/support/ .

Message.Explanation: The given JMS Destination has reached its retry limit for attempting to process a JMS message.

Message.MsgText: PCFCommandServerInvalidQueueSettingsReturned=WMSG0317E: The Command Server has returned some invalid Queue settings.

Message.MsgText: PCFCommandServerQueueManagerNotAvailable=WMSG0323E: The Queue Manager is not available.

Message.MsgText: JMSSessionCommitException=WMSG0035E: Exception committing JMS Session for MDB {0}, JMSDestination {1} : {2}

Message.MsgText: JMS_REGISTRATION_MQ_JAVA_NOT_FOUND_WMSG1625=WMSG1625E: It was not possible to detect the WebSphere MQ messaging provider code at the specified path {0}.
Message.Explanation: The WebSphere MQ messaging provider code is not installed at the specified path.
Message.UserResponse: Modify the configuration of the WebSphere MQ messaging provider in the application server so that it points to the correct path of the WebSphere MQ messaging provider. This will involve either changing the native path or install directory of the WebSphere MQ resource adapter or changing the value of the MQ_INSTALL_ROOT variable. Then restart your application server.

Message.MsgText: MQ_INSTALL_ROOT_UPDATED_PLEASE_RESTART_WMSG1622=WMSG1622E: The installation directory of the WebSphere MQ messaging provider has been updated from {0} to {1}. The WebSphere MQ messaging provider has been disabled. A server restart is required to re-enable this function.
Message.Explanation: An update has been made to the installation directory of the WebSphere MQ messaging provider.
Message.UserResponse: The application server must be restarted in order to use the client installed at the updated path.

Message.MsgText: PCFCommandServerQueueManagerStopping=WMSG0325E: The Queue Manager is stopping.
Message.Explanation: The queue manager is stopping.
Message.UserResponse: Wait for the queue manager to be restarted then try again.

Message.MsgText: ResourceBinderDisabled=WMSG0900W: JMS resource binder for resource type {0} is disabled

Message.MsgText: AFTER_DELIVERY_FAILURE_WMSG3101=WMSG3101E: An error occurred during after-delivery processing. See the linked exception for more information: {0}
Message.Explanation: This exception is unexpected. The cause is not immediately known.
Message.UserResponse: If the problem persists, additional information might be available if you search for the message ID on the following Web sites: WebSphere Application Server Support page: http://www.ibm.com/software/webservers/appserv/was/support/ WebSphere Application Server for z/OS Support page: http://www.ibm.com/software/webservers/appserv/zos_os390/support/ .

Message.MsgText: ParseException=WMSG0015E: Error parsing JMSListener config file: {0}, message: {1}
Message.Explanation: An exception was received while trying to parse the given JMS Listener configuration file.
Message.UserResponse: Correct the problem in the JMS Listener configuration file, then restart the EJB Server.

Message.MsgText: CleanedUpDurableSubscription=WMSG0053I: Redundent JMS durable subscription {0} has been unsubscribed
Message.Explanation: The durable subscription manager has determined the given subscription is now redundant, perhaps because the application has been removed. The subscription has been unsubscribed.
Message.UserResponse: No action is required.

Message.MsgText: PCFCommandServerHostNameNotSpecified=WMSG0334E: The Host name that the Queue Manager is running on is required by the WMQQueueDefiner MBean.
Message.Explanation: The WMQQueueDefiner MBean was not supplied with a host name.
Message.UserResponse: Specify the name of the host on which the queue manager is running.

Message.MsgText: JNDILookupException=WMSG0017E: Unable to lookup JMS resources, JNDI lookup exception: {0}
Message.Explanation: An exception was received performing a JNDI lookup of a JMS resource.
Message.UserResponse: Examine the exception for reasons for the problem. This might be because the given JMS resource has not being defined to the WebSphere JNDI namespace, or perhaps because the necessary JMS provider classes are not in the application server class path.

Message.MsgText: MQQueueDefinerInvalidBackoutThreshold=WMSG0104I: Invalid backout threshold specified. reason = {0}, parameter = {1}.
Message.Explanation: The backout threshold specified is not in the range 0-999999999
Message.UserResponse: Ensure that the backout threshold attribute contains a valid value.

Message.MsgText: MDBDestinationJndiNameError=WMSG0062W: The JNDI specified in the listener port ({1}) is not the same as that specifed in the bindings {2} for MDB {0}
Message.Explanation: The JNDI name for the destination in the listener port must match the destination JNDI name in the bindings.
Message.UserResponse: Ensure that the JNDI name for the destination is the same in both the listenerPort definition and the message-driven bean bindings.

Message.MsgText: MDBListenerStarted=WMSG0042I: MDB Listener {0} started successfully for JMSDestination {1}
Message.Explanation: The given MDB Listener has started successfully.
Message.UserResponse: No action is required.

Message.MsgText: BEFORE_DELIVERY_FAILURE_WMSG3100=WMSG3100E: An error occurred during before delivery processing, see linked exception for more information: {0}
Message.Explanation: This exception is unexpected. The cause is not immediately known.
Message.UserResponse: If the problem persists, additional information might be available if you search for the message ID on the following Web sites: WebSphere Application Server Support page: http://www.ibm.com/software/webservers/appserv/was/support/ WebSphere Application Server for z/OS Support page: http://www.ibm.com/software/webservers/appserv/zos_os390/support/ .

Message.MsgText: PCFCommandServerNotEnoughStorage=WMSG0312E: There is not enough main storage to perform the action.
Message.Explanation: There is not enough space available in main storage to perform the action.
Message.UserResponse: Consult the WebSphere MQ information center to correct the problem.

Message.MsgText: MDBListenerPortNotFound=WMSG0046E: Unable to find Listener Port {1} for binding MDB {0}
Message.Explanation: The binding of the specified message-driven bean to the specified listener port was unsuccessful because the listener port could not be found.
Message.UserResponse: Ensure the given listener port exists in the Message Listener Service for the given application server.

Message.MsgText: MDBPooledThreadException=WMSG0039E: Exception in MDBPooledThread: {0}
Message.Explanation: During the processing of a JMS message on a server thread an unexpected exception was received.
Message.UserResponse: Examine the exception for reasons for the problem. After correction restart the MDB EJB JAR module from the administrative console.

Message.MsgText: PCFQueueDataQueueNameSet=WMSG0338E: The Queue Name was set twice.
Message.Explanation: A queue name cannot be set twice.
Message.UserResponse: Do not specify the queue name twice.

Message.MsgText: MQQueueDefinerInvalidPriority=WMSG0101I: Invalid default priority specified. reason = {0}, parameter = {1}.
Message.Explanation: The priority specified was not in the range 0-9.
Message.UserResponse: Ensure that the priority contains a valid value.

Message.MsgText: IBM_JMS_NOT_AVAILABLE_WMSG1303=WMSG1303E: Unable to define JMS Destination {0} as neither WebSphere Embedded Messaging nor WebSphere MQ JMS is available
Message.Explanation: When attempting to define a JMS Destination to WebSphere Embedded Messaging, the required classes could not be found on this node.
Message.UserResponse: Install WebSphere Embedded Messaging or WebSphere MQ JMS on this node.

Message.MsgText: MQQueueDefinerClusterNameListTooLong=WMSG0117I: Cluster name list is over 48 characters long. reason = {0}, parameter = {1}.
Message.Explanation: The cluster name list specified is longer than 48 characters.
Message.UserResponse: Ensure that the cluster name list contains less than 48 characters.

Message.MsgText: MESSAGING_NOT_INSTALLED_WMSG1601=WMSG1601I: WebSphere MQ JMS has not been installed
Message.Explanation: WebSphere MQ JMS has not been installed on this node so will not be available.
Message.UserResponse: If WebSphere MQ JMS is to be used on this node it must be installed.

Message.MsgText: NO_WMQ_JCA_RA1_WMSG1606=WMSG1606E: An internal error occurred.
Message.Explanation: This exception is unexpected. The cause is not immediately known.
Message.UserResponse: If the problem persists, additional information might be available if you search for the message ID on the following Web sites: WebSphere Application Server Support page: http://www.ibm.com/software/webservers/appserv/was/support/ WebSphere Application Server for z/OS Support page: http://www.ibm.com/software/webservers/appserv/zos_os390/support/ .

Message.MsgText: MQQueueDefinerAuthorizationException=WMSG0100E: User is not authorised to access Command Queue
Message.Explanation: The user name and password are either not known or do not have the required access privileges.
Message.UserResponse: Check that the user name and password are correct.

Message.MsgText: PCFCommandServerMessageTooBigForQueue=WMSG0308E: The message was too big for the Queue.
Message.Explanation: The message was bigger than the maximum message length setting for the queue.
Message.UserResponse: Use WebSphere MQ tooling to increase the maximum message length of the SYSTEM.ADMIN.COMMAND.QUEUE.

Message.MsgText: MDBListenerCreateError=WMSG0021E: Exception constructing MDBListenerImpl {0}, JMSDestination {1} : {2}
Message.Explanation: An exception has occurred during the creation of an MDB Listener.
Message.UserResponse: Examine the exception for reasons for the problem, then restart the EJB Server to re-initialize the JMS Listener.

Message.MsgText: JMSListenerStartedWithWarnings=WMSG0040W: JMS Listener started with warnings
Message.Explanation: The JMS Listener service has started, however some warnings were issued during initialization.
Message.UserResponse: Examine the warnings for any problems that might need correcting.
